description: Test for voltage drop across the diode in the load module during the ON period to check if the diode is open or has high resistance, which could prevent voltage from reaching the lamps., outcome='The voltage drop across the load protection diode is approximately 0.359\u202fV (anode: 0.3592\u202fV, cathode: 0.0003\u202fV), indicating the diode is forward-biased but conducting a very small current. Both the main load lamp and the internal indicator lamp show nearly zero voltage across their terminals (0.0003\u202fV), suggesting minimal or no voltage is reaching the lamps during the ON period.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
