description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of the switched pair of the control module during both ON and OFF periods of the lamp to check if voltage is being correctly delivered downstream when the relay is closed. This helps locate whether the excessive voltage drop is in the control module or load module., outcome="Measured voltage at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V, both referenced to ground. Voltages are low at the control module output during the test. No polarity inversion detected in cable labeling in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> voltage at input terminals of control module (input pair),
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of the control module (where it receives power from the power supply module) to verify whether the expected voltage (approximately 12V) is present at the input. This will help determine if the voltage drop originates before, within, or after the control module., outcome="The voltage at 'Control Input Cable (+)' is 11.9875 V, and at 'Control Input Cable (−)' is approximately 0 V. The measured voltages indicate that the expected voltage is present at the input terminals of the control module. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> control module cable connectors,
description: Visually inspect the cable connectors between the control module and both the power supply and load modules for signs of improper seating, corrosion, damaged contacts, or loose connections. This helps determine if a poor electrical connection is causing a large voltage drop downstream of the control module., outcome='All visually inspected cables—Control Input/Output (+/−), PSU Output (+/−), and Load Input (+/−)—are successfully connected with no observable internal faults, improper seating, corrosion, damaged contacts, or loose connections. No polarity inversion was detected based on the port and labeling information provided.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> internal PCB traces and solder joints (control module, switched path),
description: Test continuity through the switched path inside the control module—from relay output to control module output terminals—by probing for continuity or excessive resistance. This will help detect any internal disconnect or high resistance (e.g., broken PCB trace or cold solder joint) causing the large voltage drop, despite the relay being functional., outcome='Diagnostic result: The tested path from Control Relay to Control Output Cable (+) shows excellent continuity, with a measured resistance of 0.01 Ω. No internal disconnect or excessive resistance was detected in this switched path.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
